00:21:38,895 --> 00:21:40,795
They said something about a murder.

274
00:21:40,830 --> 00:21:41,922
I gotta go to her.

275
00:21:41,965 --> 00:21:43,592
I gotta see if she's OK.

276
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:45,692
Back to Springwood?

277
00:21:45,735 --> 00:21:47,999
Do you want me to start having nightmares again?

278
00:21:48,038 --> 00:21:50,006
Don't start with that dream demon shit again.

279
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:53,669
OK? You know that's all just in your head.

280
00:21:53,710 --> 00:21:57,077
Yeah, yeah, and who are you, the poster boy for sanity?

281
00:21:57,113 --> 00:21:58,102
You're the one that told the cops...

282
00:21:58,148 --> 00:21:59,740
Lori's dad killed his wife.

283
00:21:59,783 --> 00:22:01,341
Yeah, right, and now it looks like someone else...

284
00:22:01,384 --> 00:22:02,510
got killed in the same house.

285
00:22:02,552 --> 00:22:04,076
You think that's a coincidence?

286
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:06,645
Two murders in one house?

287
00:22:06,690 --> 00:22:10,091
Kurt, how many times do I have to tell you, man?

288
00:22:10,126 --> 00:22:11,821
I don't do checkers.

289
00:22:11,861 --> 00:22:13,852
I'm an UNO guy, all right?

290
00:22:13,897 --> 00:22:17,833
So go grab the fucking UNO deck and we'll play, OK?

291
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:19,266
Please. Thank you.

292
00:22:21,771 --> 00:22:24,934
Look at us, Will.

293
00:22:24,974 --> 00:22:26,999
Look around you, man.

294
00:22:27,043 --> 00:22:29,034
We're institutionalized.

295
00:22:30,613 --> 00:22:33,741
We're stuck here. We're not going anywhere.

296
00:22:42,726 --> 00:22:44,819
I do miss my family, man.

297
00:22:44,861 --> 00:22:50,857
I mean, it's been four years since I've seen 'em, you know.

298
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,800
All these years, and you're still convinced...

299
00:22:52,836 --> 00:22:54,201
you saw her father do that?

300
00:22:54,237 --> 00:22:56,034
I know what I saw, Mark.

301
00:22:56,072 --> 00:22:59,200
Fuck what the doctors try to get me to believe.

302
00:22:59,242 --> 00:23:01,233
I need to know if she's OK.

303
00:23:17,994 --> 00:23:19,188
You want to play?

304
00:23:33,977 --> 00:23:36,537
Sweet dreams, monkey boy.

305
00:23:39,816 --> 00:23:41,579
What the hell was that for, man?

306
00:23:43,686 --> 00:23:45,415
Heh heh heh!

307
00:23:48,958 --> 00:23:51,290
You're a fucking lunatic, you know that?

308
00:23:51,327 --> 00:23:53,852
I know you are, but what am l?

309
00:24:10,447 --> 00:24:12,074
Are you sure you didn't see anyone?

310
00:24:12,115 --> 00:24:15,209
No, Dad, none of us did.

311
00:24:15,251 --> 00:24:18,186
I already went over this with the police.

312
00:24:25,462 --> 00:24:27,453
It's just...

313
00:24:27,497 --> 00:24:29,431
I don't know what I'd do without you.

314
00:24:29,466 --> 00:24:30,990
You're all I have left.

315
00:24:32,168 --> 00:24:34,830
Dad, I'm not going anywhere.

316
00:24:36,539 --> 00:24:38,507
I promise.

317
00:24:38,541 --> 00:24:40,839
Look at you.

318
00:24:40,877 --> 00:24:42,139
You're exhausted.

319
00:24:42,178 --> 00:24:44,874
Lori.

320
00:24:44,914 --> 00:24:47,041
We need to get you to bed!

321
00:24:49,853 --> 00:24:51,912
I don't want to go to sleep, Dad.

322
00:24:51,955 --> 00:24:53,479
I just want to see my friends.

323
00:24:53,523 --> 00:24:56,321
I don't think it's a good idea for you to go to school today.

324
00:24:56,359 --> 00:24:58,384
You've just been through a very traumatic experience.

325
00:24:58,428 --> 00:25:00,726
Dad, please...

326
00:25:00,763 --> 00:25:03,288
I just need to get out of the house, OK?

327
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:06,666
I'll be fine. I promise.

328
00:25:13,910 --> 00:25:15,844
Well, at least drink your juice.

329
00:25:21,284 --> 00:25:22,683
Will Rollins and the Davis boy...

330
00:25:22,719 --> 00:25:24,619
escaped from Westin Hills last night.

331
00:25:24,654 --> 00:25:26,918
Oh, Jesus.

332
00:25:26,956 --> 00:25:29,220
It's all coming apart again.

333
00:25:29,259 --> 00:25:31,887
Don't worry. We'll find them.

334
00:25:31,928 --> 00:25:33,987
Keep this thing contained.

335
00:25:46,142 --> 00:25:47,404
Lori!

336
00:25:47,443 --> 00:25:50,776
Oh, my God! God, you guys, I'm so glad you're here.

337
00:25:50,813 --> 00:25:52,678
Blake's dead, too.

338
00:25:52,715 --> 00:25:54,842
What?

339
00:25:54,884 --> 00:25:57,182
Yeah, he--

340
00:25:58,888 --> 00:26:02,847
He was stabbed to death late last night.

341
00:26:02,892 --> 00:26:05,019
Same with his dad.

342
00:26:05,061 --> 00:26:06,790
What?

343
00:26:08,831 --> 00:26:11,800
Shit, shit! This is bullshit!

344
00:26:11,834 --> 00:26:13,358
The police are blaming everything on Blake...

345
00:26:13,403 --> 00:26:15,428
Iike its some kind of Columbine thing or something.

346
00:26:15,471 --> 00:26:17,234
They're saying he went crazy.

347
00:26:17,273 --> 00:26:20,299
Killed Trey, killed his dad, and then took his own life?

348
00:26:20,343 --> 00:26:22,573
This is so fucking messed up.

349
00:26:22,612 --> 00:26:24,136
This is messed up.

350
00:26:25,548 --> 00:26:26,981
Excuse me. Sorry.

351
00:26:27,016 --> 00:26:28,506
Lori?

352
00:26:28,551 --> 00:26:30,018
What is it, Linderman?

353
00:26:30,053 --> 00:26:31,520
Um, well, I heard what happened,

354
00:26:31,554 --> 00:26:33,419
and I just wanted to express how, um...

355
00:26:33,456 --> 00:26:36,050
well, to tell you how sorry I was.

356
00:26:36,092 --> 00:26:38,356
Thank you. That's sweet.

357
00:26:38,394 --> 00:26:41,295
Right. Actually if you need anybody to talk to or maybe--

358
00:26:41,331 --> 00:26:43,492
Whoa, Linderman, let me give you a tip.

359
00:26:43,533 --> 00:26:45,467
Place your hormones back in the box...

360
00:26:45,501 --> 00:26:47,093
and quit while you're ahead, OK?

361
00:26:47,136 --> 00:26:48,967
We don't have time for Date-a-Dork right now.

362
00:26:49,005 --> 00:26:50,165
Thanks.

363
00:26:51,407 --> 00:26:53,170
Right. Sorry.

364
00:26:53,209 --> 00:26:55,109
I swear, every day it's the same thing.

365
00:26:55,144 --> 00:26:56,702
He's like one of those fucking froufrou dogs...

366
00:26:56,746 --> 00:26:58,179
that keeps humping your leg.

367
00:26:59,949 --> 00:27:01,348
Give a couple to some ladies.

368
00:27:01,384 --> 00:27:02,646
Thanks, man.

369
00:27:02,685 --> 00:27:03,652
I see what you're saying, Gibb...

370
00:27:03,686 --> 00:27:04,710
but that's exactly why you should go.

371
00:27:04,754 --> 00:27:06,483
I mean, be amongst friends, where it's safe.

372
00:27:06,522 --> 00:27:07,819
There's gonna be a whole lot of loving there for you...

373
00:27:07,857 --> 00:27:10,018
and my boy Trey, all right?

374
00:27:10,059 --> 00:27:11,754
Yeah. Yeah, you're right. I should go.

375
00:27:11,794 --> 00:27:13,591
I could use a few dozen drinks.

376
00:27:13,630 --> 00:27:14,597
That a girl.

377
00:27:14,631 --> 00:27:16,428
Let your freak flag fly.

378
00:27:16,466 --> 00:27:18,058
See you there.

379
00:27:18,101 --> 00:27:19,090
You want to go?

380
00:27:19,135 --> 00:27:21,035
No, I don't think so.

381
00:27:21,070 --> 00:27:23,538
I--I didn't get much sleep last night...

382
00:27:23,573 --> 00:27:25,040
and when I did sleep...

383
00:27:25,074 --> 00:27:26,701
I had the most terrible nightmares.

384
00:27:26,743 --> 00:27:28,904
Lori, you had to sleep at a police station.

385
00:27:28,945 --> 00:27:30,310
I'd have nightmares, too.

386
00:27:30,346 --> 00:27:31,870
No, no, no, it wasn't like that.

387
00:27:31,914 --> 00:27:33,848
I mean, this was really real.

388
00:27:33,883 --> 00:27:35,510
I mean, there was this man...

389
00:27:35,551 --> 00:27:37,576
but he more like a monster really...

390
00:27:37,620 --> 00:27:38,985
and they kept calling him Freddy...

391
00:27:39,022 --> 00:27:40,819
-and he was so real. -Shh!

392
00:27:40,857 --> 00:27:42,222
What did he look like?

393
00:27:42,258 --> 00:27:45,056
He--he had this...

394
00:27:45,094 --> 00:27:46,925
dark brown hat, and...

395
00:27:46,963 --> 00:27:49,363
his skin was terribly burnt...

396
00:27:49,399 --> 00:27:51,731
and on this right hand he had this like these...

397
00:27:51,768 --> 00:27:53,258
razor fingers, and--

398
00:27:53,302 --> 00:27:54,599
You must be tripping.

399
00:27:54,637 --> 00:27:55,797
No, no, no!

400
00:27:55,838 --> 00:27:57,237
And then there were these little girls...

401
00:27:57,273 --> 00:27:59,070
It's OK. It was a bad dream.

402
00:27:59,108 --> 00:28:01,440
They were singing like this--this song like--

403
00:28:01,477 --> 00:28:06,608
One, two, Freddy's coming for you.

404
00:28:06,649 --> 00:28:08,742
You know why they sing that?

405
00:28:08,785 --> 00:28:11,345
Because that's when he comes for you...

406
00:28:11,387 --> 00:28:13,355
in your dreams.

407
00:28:13,389 --> 00:28:15,550
You're lucky to be alive.

408
00:28:15,591 --> 00:28:16,819
Who is he?

409
00:28:16,859 --> 00:28:18,417
He's a child murderer...

410
00:28:18,461 --> 00:28:20,520
that some parents from around here burned alive...

411
00:28:20,563 --> 00:28:22,827
but then he came back.

412
00:28:22,865 --> 00:28:26,198
Back for revenge in our nightmares.

413
00:28:26,235 --> 00:28:27,896
Funny no one ever told us about him, huh?

414
00:28:27,937 --> 00:28:29,165
-OK, thank you! -No!

415
00:28:29,205 --> 00:28:30,297
You want some free advice?

416
00:28:30,339 --> 00:28:32,170
Coffee. Make friends with it.

417
00:28:32,208 --> 00:28:33,766
Mark!

418
00:28:33,810 --> 00:28:34,970
That's enough.

419
00:28:36,512 --> 00:28:38,036
You're scaring her.

420
00:28:42,085 --> 00:28:44,246
Will?

421
00:28:44,287 --> 00:28:46,448
Hey.

422
00:28:50,059 --> 00:28:53,051
I thought you might be in trouble, so we--

423
00:28:53,096 --> 00:28:54,586
Lori! Oh, my God!

424
00:28:54,630 --> 00:28:55,756
Lori, honey, wake up!

425
00:28:55,798 --> 00:28:58,266
Someone get help, please!

426
00:28:58,301 --> 00:28:59,893
Someone get some help, please!

427
00:28:59,936 --> 00:29:03,929
The principal! Will, let's go, let's go!

428
00:29:03,973 --> 00:29:05,736
Please, somebody help her. Lori?

429
00:29:14,183 --> 00:29:16,583
How much longer is it gonna take?

430
00:29:16,619 --> 00:29:18,246
-ls she OK or what? -Shh!

431
00:29:18,287 --> 00:29:20,084
Tsk!

432
00:29:43,312 --> 00:29:46,145
For nose jobs, what kind of anesthesia...

433
00:29:46,182 --> 00:29:47,809
do the doctors use?

434
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:49,511
They put you all the way under, right?

435
00:30:04,333 --> 00:30:05,630
Got your nose!

436
00:30:12,708 --> 00:30:14,300
Strong work, man.

437
00:30:14,343 --> 00:30:15,469
I came to make sure she's OK...

438
00:30:15,511 --> 00:30:17,843
and you put her in the infirmary.

439
00:30:21,484 --> 00:30:22,974
What were you thinking about...

440
00:30:23,019 --> 00:30:24,782
telling her all that stuff, man?

441
00:30:24,821 --> 00:30:26,049
I mean, we're not in group.

442
00:30:26,088 --> 00:30:27,248
Because I'm thinking for the first time in my life...

443
00:30:27,290 --> 00:30:29,190
that maybe I'm not crazy...

444
00:30:29,225 --> 00:30:30,715
that my brother wasn't crazy.

445
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,728
She had the same dream, Will.

446
00:30:32,762 --> 00:30:34,730
Will Rollins! Mark Davis!

447
00:30:45,141 --> 00:30:46,574
This doesn't make any sense.

448
00:30:46,609 --> 00:30:48,008
There's nothing on Krueger.

449
00:30:48,044 --> 00:30:51,070
Not his arrest, his death, not even a birth certificate.

450
00:30:51,113 --> 00:30:53,843
Whole sections of the records are gone.

451
00:30:53,883 --> 00:30:57,182
Look at all these blacked-out obituaries.

452
00:31:05,161 --> 00:31:06,890
January eighteenth.

453
00:31:06,929 --> 00:31:10,228
That's the day my brother committed suicide.

454
00:31:10,266 --> 00:31:12,257
Why isn't that in here?

455
00:31:14,237 --> 00:31:16,967
I don't know!

456
00:31:17,006 --> 00:31:19,338
But I'm sure there's a good reason.

457
00:31:20,776 --> 00:31:22,300
Remember in group when they told us...

458
00:31:22,345 --> 00:31:23,710
not to jump to conclusions?

459
00:31:23,746 --> 00:31:24,906
Listen to yourself.

460
00:31:24,947 --> 00:31:26,778
You're holding onto that psychobabble bullshit...

461
00:31:26,816 --> 00:31:29,376
Iike it's some kind of security blanket, man.

462
00:31:29,418 --> 00:31:33,047
Let it go. They've covered him up, Will.

463
00:31:33,089 --> 00:31:34,522
They never told us about Freddy...

464
00:31:34,557 --> 00:31:36,457
because that's how they decided to beat him.

465
00:31:36,492 --> 00:31:39,393
They treated him like he was a fucking disease...

466
00:31:39,428 --> 00:31:40,452
and they locked up all the kids...

467
00:31:40,496 --> 00:31:41,463
who had made contact with him...

468
00:31:41,497 --> 00:31:43,226
so they wouldn't infect the others.

469
00:31:43,266 --> 00:31:44,460
That's crazy.

470
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:46,968
Is it?

471
00:31:47,003 --> 00:31:49,267
How come we were never allowed...

472
00:31:49,305 --> 00:31:51,773
to call any of our friends, man?

473
00:31:51,807 --> 00:31:54,207
How come none of our friends ever called us?

474
00:31:54,243 --> 00:31:57,269
We were in a fucking quarantine, man.

475
00:31:57,313 --> 00:31:59,781
That's what Westin Hills was for.

476
00:31:59,815 --> 00:32:02,181
Well, even if all you're saying is true...

477
00:32:02,218 --> 00:32:04,618
then why didn't Freddy kill Lori?

478
00:32:04,654 --> 00:32:07,214
Maybe he's not strong enough yet.

479
00:32:07,256 --> 00:32:09,884
My brother said it's our fear that gives him his power.

480
00:32:09,926 --> 00:32:11,257
Yeah, well, you sure as hell...

481
00:32:11,294 --> 00:32:13,785
spread enough fear today at school.

482
00:32:13,829 --> 00:32:15,820
Holy shit.

483
00:32:20,169 --> 00:32:21,431
You're right.

484
00:32:21,470 --> 00:32:25,634
They wanted to forget Freddy so they wouldn't fear him.

485
00:32:25,675 --> 00:32:28,269
What if I screwed up the town's plan?

486
00:32:29,545 --> 00:32:32,343
Fuck! This fucker's gonna spread like the plague, man!

487
00:32:32,381 --> 00:32:35,612
Kids are gonna start falling asleep, it's gonna--

488
00:32:35,651 --> 00:32:37,084
Let's leave, man. Let's leave right now.

489
00:32:37,119 --> 00:32:38,086
No, I can't leave.

490
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,280
Why not?

491
00:32:39,322 --> 00:32:41,256
I gotta go talk to Lori. I gotta see if she's OK.

492
00:32:41,290 --> 00:32:42,587
Well, is she worth dying for?

493
00:32:42,625 --> 00:32:45,150
Because if you fall asleep, you ain't waking up.

494
00:32:45,194 --> 00:32:48,493
If that's the case, how come you're not dead?

495
00:32:48,531 --> 00:32:49,725
Or any of the freaks at Westin?

496
00:32:49,765 --> 00:32:52,996
When's the last time you even had a nightmare?

497
00:32:53,035 --> 00:32:54,525
I don't know.

498
00:32:54,570 --> 00:32:56,504
I can't remember my dreams anymore.

499
00:32:58,040 --> 00:33:01,066
Look, just give me one night, OK?

500
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:04,045
Just let me find Lori, and then we're out of here.

501
00:33:05,514 --> 00:33:07,539
I swear.

502
00:33:08,818 --> 00:33:09,876
All right.

503
00:33:09,919 --> 00:33:11,716
If your ass isn't back here by dawn, I'm gone.

504
00:33:11,754 --> 00:33:14,780
We clear on that?

505
00:33:14,824 --> 00:33:18,658
This baby's my brother's pride and joy, so be careful.

506
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,384
Oh, shit.

507
00:33:52,428 --> 00:33:53,417
Linderman!

508
00:33:53,462 --> 00:33:56,522
Shack, I don't drink.

509
00:34:15,851 --> 00:34:19,378
Hi, Lori. Didn't think I'd see you here.

510
00:34:19,422 --> 00:34:21,117
Can I get you something to drink?

511
00:34:21,157 --> 00:34:24,786
Smooth opening, but, you know, we're already taken care of.

512
00:34:24,827 --> 00:34:27,159
What happened to your clothes?

513
00:34:27,196 --> 00:34:29,289
Oh, this.

514
00:34:29,331 --> 00:34:30,423
I was playing a drinking game...

515
00:34:30,466 --> 00:34:33,799
with some of the lower primates...

516
00:34:33,836 --> 00:34:35,326
and I guess I'm penalized for my ability...

517
00:34:35,371 --> 00:34:36,998
to read above a fourth-grade level.

518
00:34:37,039 --> 00:34:38,768
Linderman, you know, I always pictured you...

519
00:34:38,808 --> 00:34:41,299
as a straight up bedwetter.

520
00:34:41,343 --> 00:34:43,311
You know what, Kia?

521
00:34:43,345 --> 00:34:44,812
I used to think you hated me...

522
00:34:44,847 --> 00:34:46,576
because you thought I wasn't good enough for Lori...

523
00:34:46,615 --> 00:34:47,877
but that's not it.

524
00:34:47,917 --> 00:34:50,147
You tear me down to make yourself feel better...

525
00:34:50,186 --> 00:34:51,585
because you really hate yourself...

526
00:34:51,620 --> 00:34:53,315
which is kind of pathetic when you actually...

527
00:34:53,355 --> 00:34:54,515
stop and think about it, assuming, of course...

528
00:34:54,557 --> 00:34:56,388
you can think with all that makeup...

529
00:34:56,425 --> 00:34:58,450
weighing down your head.

530
00:35:04,433 --> 00:35:06,424
The cops said Blake committed suicide.

531
00:35:06,469 --> 00:35:08,027
Apparently, it was grief over Trey.

532
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:09,298
No, man, that's bullshit.

533
00:35:09,338 --> 00:35:11,306
I heard some guy Krueger killed them both.

534
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:13,308
Said his name to my parents, they almost shit themselves.

535
00:35:13,342 --> 00:35:14,309
Yeah, yeah, yeah, man, and I heard...

536
00:35:14,343 --> 00:35:15,810
that Freddy freak, he used to live here.

537
00:35:15,845 --> 00:35:18,279
Fucking gutted Trey like a Goddamn turkey, man.

538
00:35:18,314 --> 00:35:22,250
Like I heard his intestines and shit was on the floor--

539
00:35:22,284 --> 00:35:25,447
